cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper is about fault tolerance in enterprise networks, which typically involve the use of middleboxes to form a service function chain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the implementation and evaluation of a prototype system, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper deals with ensuring consistency and reliability in the face of failures, which could also place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves the collection and replication of state updates, which could be seen as a data management problem, placing it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
